import React from "react"; import PropTypes from "prop-types"; class ProPTypes extends React.Component { render() { return (

ReactJS Props Validate

Type Value Valid
Array {JSON.stringify(this.props.propArray)} {Array.isArray(this.props.propArray) ? "True" : "False"}
Boolean {this.props.propBool.toString()} {typeof this.props.propBool === "boolean" ? "True" : "False"}
Function {this.props.propFunc(5)} {typeof this.props.propFunc === "function" ? "True" : "False"}
String {this.props.propString} {typeof this.props.propString === "string" ? "True" : "False"}
Number {this.props.propNumber} {typeof this.props.propNumber === "number" ? "True" : "False"}
); } } ProPTypes.propTypes = { propArray: PropTypes.array.isRequired, propBool: PropTypes.bool.isRequired, propFunc: PropTypes.func.isRequired, // Updated to expect a function propString: PropTypes.string, propNumber: PropTypes.number }; ProPTypes.defaultProps = { propArray: [1, 2, 3, 4, 5], propBool: true, propFunc: x => x + 5, // Default function returns x + 5 propString: "Props", propNumber: 1 }; export default ProPTypes;
